{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05525/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05525"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:55:25"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man steps out into a hotel room entryway as another man stands in the doorway."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05525","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05525"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/canvas/1/6aa70c64-98ec-4395-95bf-96444ee5d3dc","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-26T19:54:33.775Z","creator":"Alice Tweedy McGrath","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Although Cal’s character isn’t developed much in the film, he appears somewhat cowardly and reticent to take action in his mother’s affairs. The real-life figure he was based on, Lance Reventlow, son of Barbara Hutton, had a similarly peculiar relationship with his mother. Take, for instance, the following report from C. David Haymann’s biography of Hutton: “After a week they were back in Paris, staying in Barbara’s suite. Two weeks later, they decided to take in the international polo championships. Barbara went along for the ride. The French press accused her of chaperoning her son in an effort to frighten off the young female aspirants interested in his inheritance. Lance was evidently susceptible. He had recently been emotionally involved with a certain high-priced California call girl. When the lady discovered the identity of her John she suddenly became possessive, and it took a substantial sum of Barbara’s money to pry her loose” (Haymann, <em>Poor Little Rich Girl</em>, 285).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05525/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:982.3674521354937,64.89046391752575,380.5387058173783,430.4243372606774"}}}]}]}]}